@startuml
title Chapter 4 · Permission Decision Layers

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam dpi 135
skinparam ranksep 38
skinparam nodesep 26
skinparam defaultFontName Georgia
skinparam defaultFontSize 15
skinparam TitleFontSize 20
skinparam NoteFontSize 14
skinparam ArrowFontSize 13
skinparam TitleFontColor #161616
skinparam rectangle {
  BackgroundColor #F2E9D9
  BorderColor #1D1D1D
  FontColor #161616
  RoundCorner 10
}
skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #F5EBDD
  BorderColor #8C2721
  FontColor #7B1E1E
}
skinparam ArrowColor #5E5A53

rectangle "Tool request" as Request #EFE6D8
rectangle "Rules layer\nallow / deny / ask" as Rules #E8DDD0
rectangle "Mode layer\nbypass / plan /\nauto / default" as Modes #E8DDD0
rectangle "Automated checks\nclassifier / hooks /\npolicy gates" as Checks #EFE6D8
rectangle "Interactive approval\nonly when runtime\nshould not decide" as Dialog #F3E6CD
rectangle "Final result\nALLOW or DENY" as Result #EFE6D8

Request --> Rules
Rules --> Modes
Modes --> Checks
Checks --> Dialog
Dialog --> Result
Rules --> Result : hard deny
Modes --> Result : bypass allow
Checks --> Result : clear auto decision

note right of Rules
  Claude Code keeps an
  explicit ask path.
  Intent is not the same as
  authorization.
end note

@enduml
